icologists. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "heirs of a man who has left neither parent nor offspring:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [particularly], with respect to the [portions of inheritances termed]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faraAy^iD", "text_ar": "فَرَايِض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fariyDapN", "text_ar": "فَرِيضَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "q. v.],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "all such as have not a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fariyDap", "text_ar": "فَرِيضَة"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "named, and who receive if there remain anything after"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the distribution of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faraAy^iD", "text_ar": "فَرَايِض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K, TA:) thus accord. to those who treat of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "frAy^D", "text_ar": "فرايض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and accord. to the [other] lawyers: (TA:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "relations by the side of the males:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "this is the meaning of what is said by the leading lexicologists: (Msb:) or, as is said by Az, a man's"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "heirs consisting of male relations:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, TA:) or his"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sons, and relations on the father's side:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) so called because they encompass him; the father being a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Taraf", "text_ar": "طَرَف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. an extremity in the right line], and so the son, and the paternal uncle being a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaAnib", "text_ar": "جَانِب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. a collateral relation], and so the brother: (Az, S, TA:) or a man's"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "relations on the father's side;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, TA;) because they encompass him and he is strengthened by them: (TA:) afterwards it became applied to a single person as well as to a pl. number, and both a male and a female: (Mgh:) or the lawyers apply it to a single person when there is no other than he, because he stands in the place of the collective number in receiving the whole of the property; and in the language of the law it is applied to a female in certain cases relating to emancipation and inheritances, but not otherwise either in the proper language or in the language of the law: (Msb:) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuSuwbapN", "text_ar": "عُصُوبَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is used as its inf. n. [meaning the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "state of being persons,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a person, to whom the term"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaSabapN", "text_ar": "عَصَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is applied"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Mgh:) it is said [by Az] in the T, “ I have not heard any sing. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaSabapN", "text_ar": "عَصَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": accord. to analogy it should be"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaASibN", "text_ar": "عَاصِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TaAlibN", "text_ar": "طَالِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is sing. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TalabapN", "text_ar": "طَلَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": ” (TA: [and the like is also said in the Mgh: in the Msb it is said that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaSabapN", "text_ar": "عَصَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaASibN", "text_ar": "عَاصِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kafarapN", "text_ar": "كَفَرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAfirN", "text_ar": "كَافِرٌ"}, {"kind